            "style": "",
            "text": "[T]he clear pattern is that tech companies have uniformly adopted a strategy of obfuscating information behind background. It’s also easy to see why companies like to abuse background: They can provide their point of view to the media without being accountable for it. Instead, journalists have to act like they magically know things, and readers have to guess who is trustworthy and who is not. This is bad, so we’re going to reset these expectations as loudly as possible. From now on, the default for communications professionals and people speaking to ",
